Lotus halophilus

    Authority   Boiss.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Fabales:Leguminosae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 7413

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A small, silvery pubescent, herbaceous legume
   reaching 6-12 cm in height with narrow elliptical leaflets,
   lemon-yellow flowers and with a broad, slightly flattened pod. USES
   Used as pasture for cattle and sheep. GROWING PERIOD Annual. COMMON
   NAMES Pretty birdsfoot trefoil, Qurn-al-ghazzal. FURTHER INF Pretty
   birdsfoot trefoil occurs in southeasten Mediterranean Europe, western
   Asia and Mediterranean Africa. It is common on sandy soils, dunes,
   wadis and sandy pockets in sandstone. (pH estimated by the compiler).

   Sources
   Kernick M 1978 pp 573-595 [RAIN, KTMP, DRA, TEXT, TEMP]

